## Rerun

If your memory indicates this task already completed successfully and
you have access to the prior attempt, you may assume nothing has
changed. Follow this procedure:

1. `put_test_raw` your last-attempt test source.
2. Reapply any skips your memory recorded.
3. Reapply any `expect_test_failure` markings your memory recorded.
4. Run `forge_test` to re-stamp the publish gate.
5. Reinvoke the feedback tool to re-stamp the judge's acceptance (the
   judge retains its memory of prior rounds, so re-acceptance of an
   unchanged draft is cheap).
6. Deliver via `result`.

Do NOT skip steps 4 and 5 -- the publish gate requires both stamps on the
*current* buffer.
